      "text": "[{\"id\":22,\"author\":\"user\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"You are an expert product designer, UX architect, and full-stack engineer.\\n\\nGoal:\\nCreate a NEW, fully functional, mobile-first web application called “Armor” whose UX structure, layout patterns, navigation model, and interaction flow are inspired by the public website:\\nhttps://www.fighterverses.com\\n\\nYou may analyze the URL and any provided screenshots for structural reference only.\\n\\nHard constraints:\\n- Do NOT copy branding, copy text, visuals, names, or assets.\\n- Do NOT replicate pixel-level design.\\n- Do NOT reuse wording or Bible-specific language.\\n- Use original UI, original copy, and neutral placeholder content.\\n- The result must be a runnable, deployable app.\\n\\nTarget platform:\\n- Mobile-first responsive web app\\n- Scales cleanly to full desktop website\\n\\nTech requirements:\\n- Choose a modern, production-ready stack suitable for deployment\\n- Include auth, persistence, and routing\\n- Use realistic placeholder data\\n- Include installable PWA support if appropriate\\n\\nFunctional requirements (inspired by structure, not content):\\n- Home screen with a primary featured item\\n- Practice / interaction flow with progress tracking\\n- Quiz or challenge mechanics\\n- User-created lists or collections\\n- Review or repetition scheduling logic\\n- Settings / preferences\\n- Content or resources section\\n- Empty, loading, and error states on all screens\\n\\nUX/UI requirements:\\n- Clear navigation model (tabs, drawer, or hybrid — justify choice)\\n- Consistent spacing and hierarchy\\n- Reusable component system\\n- Accessible (keyboard, ARIA, contrast)\\n- Mobile ergonomics prioritized\\n\\nDeliverables:\\n1. Complete runnable project (all files)\\n2. Folder structure\\n3. Clear local run instructions\\n4. Clear deploy instructions\\n5. Seed/sample data\\n6. Brief explanation of the UX structure chosen\\n\\nOutput the full project code. Do not stop at wireframes or descriptions.\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\"files\":[\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"ArmorApp_ArmorSetA.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":36399,\\\"lastModified\\\":1546494692000,\\\"data\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"ArmorApp_SetReferenceTable.csv\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"text/csv\\\",\\\"size\\\":10941,\\\"lastModified\\\":1766890715000,\\\"data\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"ArmorApp_ArmorSetB.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":37782,\\\"lastModified\\\":1546494701000,\\\"data\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"ArmorApp_ArmorSetC.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":27331,\\\"lastModified\\\":1546494710000,\\\"data\\\":\\\"\u003d\u003d\\\"}\",\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"ArmorApp_ArmorSetE.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":33857,\\\"lastModified\\\":1546494731000,\\\"data\\\":\\\"\u003d\\\"}\",\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"ArmorApp_ArmorSetD.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":35882,\\\"lastModified\\\":1546494719000,\\\"data\\\":\\\"\u003d\\\"}\"],\"fileUploads\":[],\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":1766892867026},{\"id\":23,\"author\":\"model\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"text\":\"**Defining \\\"Armor\\\" App**\\n\\nI\u0027ve been solidifying the initial vision for this \\\"Armor\\\" app. It\u0027s taking shape as a full-stack React application, drawing inspiration from fighterverses.com\u0027s structure, but with completely original content. I\u0027m aiming for a neutral subject matter that still provides an engaging memory/learning experience. The home screen is the focus right now.\\n\\n\\n**Exploring Core App Features**\\n\\nI\u0027m now diving into the core app features. I\u0027m focusing on the practice and interaction flow, considering progress tracking and adding quiz mechanics, and also how user collections and lists will function. Review scheduling and settings are also on the roadmap, but I\u0027ll focus on these initial three things now. I\u0027m taking notes on UX, and the architecture is taking form.\\n\\n\\n**Designing Interaction Modes**\\n\\nI\u0027m now zeroing in on the interaction modes for learning. I\u0027m imagining modes such as \\\"Read,\\\" \\\"Quiz,\\\" and \\\"Fill in the Blanks.\\\" I\u0027m also planning the data structure, how the file structure will work, the file names. I will be incorporating the React front end, as well as the initial types.\\n\\n\\n**Planning Core Features Implementation**\\n\\nI\u0027m solidifying the implementation steps. I\u0027m starting with a simple mock authentication using local storage. I\u0027ll persist progress data there as well. Spaced repetition will be handled with basic logic: correct answers advance review dates. I\u0027m focusing on \\\"Hide Words\\\" and \\\"Multiple Choice\\\" quiz types for now. I\u0027ve broken down the implementation into clear stages: setup, types/constants, state management, reusable components, and the crucial pages (\\\"Home,\\\" \\\"Library,\\\" \\\"MyCollection,\\\" \\\"Practice\\\"), all built on `react-router-dom`. The \u0027Practice\u0027 mode will include Read, Blur, and First Letter modes.\\n\\n\\n**Building Practice View**\\n\\nI\u0027m now focusing on refining the \\\"Practice\\\" view. I\u0027m prioritizing the interactive elements, specifically the \\\"Masking\\\" toggle and a \\\"Quiz\\\" mode where users select the missing word. I\u0027m keeping the design clean and dark-mode compatible. I\u0027m also planning to incorporate a slider to progressively hide words based on difficulty. I have a firm checklist and a high confidence score for success. I\u0027ve drafted content including metadata, HTML, types, constants, and the app\u0027s structural components.\\n\\n\\n**Integrating Visualizations for Progress**\\n\\nI\u0027ve been planning the \\\"Stats\\\" section of the Home page, where I\u0027ll integrate a simple progress visualization using `recharts`. This will fulfill the visualization requirement and provide users with immediate feedback on their learning journey. I\u0027m focusing on simplicity and clarity in the chart design, ensuring it complements the overall aesthetic I am using, a clean, neutral slate.\\n\\n\\n\",\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":1766892867026,\"doneTimestamp\":1766892885419},{\"id\":24,\"author\":\"model\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The following XML block contains the complete source code for \\\"Armor\\\", a mobile-first progressive web application designed for memory retention and wisdom accumulation.\\n\\nThis project implements a full \\\"Spaced Repetition\\\" learning system using React, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS. It features persistent local storage, progress visualization, and a \\\"Masking\\\" engine for memorization practice.\\n\\n\",\"cMarkNode\":{}},\"createdTimestamp\":1766892885419,\"doneTimestamp\":1766892885448},{\"id\":25,\"author\":\"model\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"generationTable\",\"entries\":[{\"path\":\"metadata.json\",\"generationType\":0,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"App metadata and description\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"{\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"Armor\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"A mobile-first memory retention application designed to build mental resilience through the internalization of wisdom, poetry, and quotes. Features spaced repetition, interactive practice modes, and progress tracking.\\\"\\n}\"}]},{\"path\":\"index.html\",\"generationType\":0,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"Root HTML file with Tailwind CSS and viewport settings\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"\u003c!DOCTYPE html\u003e\\n\u003chtml lang\u003d\\\"en\\\"\u003e\\n  \u003chead\u003e\\n    \u003cmeta charset\u003d\\\"UTF-8\\\" /\u003e\\n    \u003cmeta name\u003d\\\"viewport\\\" content\u003d\\\"width\u003ddevice-width, initial-scale\u003d1.0, maximum-scale\u003d1.0, user-scalable\u003dno\\\" /\u003e\\n    \u003ctitle\u003eArmor - Mental Resilience\u003c/title\u003e\\n    \u003cscript src\u003d\\\"https://cdn.tailwindcss.com\\\"\u003e\u003c/script\u003e\\n    \u003cscript\u003e\\n      tailwind.config \u003d {\\n        theme: {\\n          extend: {\\n            colors: {\\n              slate: {\\n                850: \u0027#1e293b\u0027,\\n                900: \u0027#0f172a\u0027,\\n              },\\n              primary: {\\n                50: \u0027#f0f9ff\u0027,\\n                100: \u0027#e0f2fe\u0027,\\n                500: \u0027#0ea5e9\u0027,\\n                600: \u0027#0284c7\u0027,\\n                700: \u0027#0369a1\u0027,\\n              }\\n            },\\n            fontFamily: {\\n              sans: [\u0027Inter\u0027, \u0027system-ui\u0027, \u0027sans-serif\u0027],\\n              serif: [\u0027Merriweather\u0027, \u0027serif\u0027],\\n            }\\n          }\\n        }\\n      }\\n    \u003c/script\u003e\\n    \u003cstyle\u003e\\n      body {\\n        background-color: #f8fafc;\\n        -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\\n      }\\n      /* Hide scrollbar for clean UI in horizontal lists */\\n      .no-scrollbar::-webkit-scrollbar {\\n        display: none;\\n      }\\n      .no-scrollbar {\\n        -ms-overflow-style: none;\\n        scrollbar-width: none;\\n      }\\n    \u003c/style\u003e\\n  \u003c/head\u003e\\n  \u003cbody\u003e\\n    \u003cdiv id\u003d\\\"root\\\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\\n  \u003c/body\u003e\\n\u003c/html\u003e\"}]},{\"path\":\"types.ts\",\"generationType\":0,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"TypeScript definitions for the application data models\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"export enum Difficulty {\\n  Easy \u003d \u0027EASY\u0027,\\n  Medium \u003d \u0027MEDIUM\u0027,\\n  Hard \u003d \u0027HARD\u0027\\n}\\n\\nexport interface Item {\\n  id: string;\\n  title: string;\\n  author: string;\\n  text: string;\\n  category: string;\\n  difficulty: Difficulty;\\n}\\n\\nexport interface UserProgress {\\n  itemId: string;\\n  nextReview: number; // Timestamp\\n  interval: number; // Days\\n  masteryLevel: number; // 0-5\\n  lastPracticed: number; // Timestamp\\n}\\n\\nexport interface UserState {\\n  savedItems: string[]; // List of Item IDs\\n  progress: Record\u003cstring, UserProgress\u003e;\\n  streak: number;\\n  lastVisit: number;\\n}\\n\\nexport interface StoreContextType {\\n  items: Item[];\\n  savedItems: string[];\\n  progress: Record\u003cstring, UserProgress\u003e;\\n  toggleSaveItem: (id: string) \u003d\u003e void;\\n  logPractice: (id: string, success: boolean) \u003d\u003e void;\\n  getDueItems: () \u003d\u003e Item[];\\n}\\n\"}]},{\"path\":\"constants.ts\",\"generationType\":0,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"Seed data and configuration constants\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"import { Item, Difficulty } from \u0027./types\u0027;\\n\\nexport const SEED_ITEMS: Item[] \u003d [\\n  {\\n    id: \u00271\u0027,\\n    title: \u0027On Shortness of Life\u0027,\\n    author: \u0027Seneca\u0027,\\n    text: \u0027It is not that we have a short time to live, but that we waste a lot of it. Life is long enough, and a sufficiently generous amount has been given to us for the highest achievements if it were all well invested.\u0027,\\n    category: \u0027Stoicism\u0027,\\n    difficulty: Difficulty.Medium\\n  },\\n  {\\n    id: \u00272\u0027,\\n    title: \u0027The Road Not Taken\u0027,\\n    author: \u0027Robert Frost\u0027,\\n    text: \u0027Two roads diverged in a wood, and I—\\\\nI took the one less traveled by,\\\\nAnd that has made all the difference.\u0027,\\n    category: \u0027Poetry\u0027,\\n    difficulty: Difficulty.Easy\\n  },\\n  {\\n    id: \u00273\u0027,\\n    title: \u0027Invictus\u0027,\\n    author: \u0027William Ernest Henley\u0027,\\n    text: \u0027It matters not how strait the gate,\\\\nHow charged with punishments the scroll,\\\\nI am the master of my fate,\\\\nI am the captain of my soul.\u0027,\\n    category: \u0027Poetry\u0027,\\n    difficulty: Difficulty.Medium\\n  },\\n  {\\n    id: \u00274\u0027,\\n    title: \u0027Meditations 2.1\u0027,\\n    author: \u0027Marcus Aurelius\u0027,\\n    text: \u0027When you wake up in the morning, tell yourself: The people I deal with today will be meddling, ungrateful, arrogant, dishonest, jealous, and surly. They are like this because they can\\\\\u0027t tell good from evil.\u0027,\\n    category: \u0027Stoicism\u0027,\\n    difficulty: Difficulty.Hard\\n  },\\n  {\\n    id: \u00275\u0027,\\n    title: \u0027Dune Litany\u0027,\\n    author: \u0027Frank Herbert\u0027,\\n    text: \u0027I must not fear. Fear is the mind-killer. Fear is the little-death that brings total obliteration. I will face my fear. I will permit it to pass over me and through me.\u0027,\\n    category: \u0027Literature\u0027,\\n    difficulty: Difficulty.Medium\\n  },\\n  {\\n    id: \u00276\u0027,\\n    title: \u0027Ozymandias\u0027,\\n    author: \u0027Percy Bysshe Shelley\u0027,\\n    text: \u0027My name is Ozymandias, King of Kings;\\\\nLook on my Works, ye Mighty, and despair!\\\\nNothing beside remains. Round the decay\\\\nOf that colossal Wreck, boundless and bare\\\\nThe lone and level sands stretch far away.\u0027,\\n    category: \u0027Poetry\u0027,\\n    difficulty: Difficulty.Hard\\n  },\\n  {\\n    id: \u00277\u0027,\\n    title: \u0027Be Water\u0027,\\n    author: \u0027Bruce Lee\u0027,\\n    text: \u0027Empty your mind, be formless, shapeless — like water. Now you put water in a cup, it becomes the cup; You put water into a bottle it becomes the bottle; You put it in a teapot it becomes the teapot. Now water can flow or it can crash. Be water, my friend.\u0027,\\n    category: \u0027Philosophy\u0027,\\n    difficulty: Difficulty.Medium\\n  }\\n];\\n\\nexport const APP_NAME \u003d \\\"Armor\\\";\\n\"}]},{\"path\":\"context/StoreContext.tsx\",\"generationType\":0,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"Global state management using React Context and LocalStorage\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"import React, { createContext, useContext, useState, useEffect } from \u0027react\u0027;\\nimport { Item, UserState, StoreContextType, UserProgress } from \u0027../types\u0027;\\nimport { SEED_ITEMS } from \u0027../constants\u0027;\\n\\nconst StoreContext \u003d createContext\u003cStoreContextType | undefined\u003e(undefined);\\n\\nconst LOCAL_STORAGE_KEY \u003d \u0027armor_app_state_v1\u0027;\\n\\nconst INITIAL_STATE: UserState \u003d {\\n  savedItems: [\u00271\u0027, \u00273\u0027], // Pre-select a couple for the user\\n  progress: {},\\n  streak: 0,\\n  lastVisit: Date.now(),\\n};\\n\\nexport const StoreProvider: React.FC\u003c{ children: React.ReactNode }\u003e \u003d ({ children }) \u003d\u003e {\\n  const [items] \u003d useState\u003cItem[]\u003e(SEED_ITEMS);\\n  const [userState, setUserState] \u003d useState\u003cUserState\u003e(INITIAL_STATE);\\n  const [isLoaded, setIsLoaded] \u003d useState(false);\\n\\n  // Load from LocalStorage\\n  useEffect(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    try {\\n      const stored \u003d localStorage.getItem(LOCAL_STORAGE_KEY);\\n      if (stored) {\\n        setUserState(JSON.parse(stored));\\n      }\\n    } catch (e) {\\n      console.error(\\\"Failed to load persistence\\\", e);\\n    } finally {\\n      setIsLoaded(true);\\n    }\\n  }, []);\\n\\n  // Save to LocalStorage\\n  useEffect(() \u003d\u003e {\\n    if (isLoaded) {\\n      localStorage.setItem(LOCAL_STORAGE_KEY, JSON.stringify(userState));\\n    }\\n  }, [userState, isLoaded]);\\n\\n  const toggleSaveItem \u003d (id: string) \u003d\u003e {\\n    setUserState(prev \u003d\u003e {\\n      const isSaved \u003d prev.savedItems.includes(id);\\n      let newSaved;\\n      if (isSaved) {\\n        newSaved \u003d prev.savedItems.filter(i \u003d\u003e i !\u003d\u003d id);\\n      } else {\\n        newSaved \u003d [...prev.savedItems, id];\\n      }\\n      return { ...prev, savedItems: newSaved };\\n    });\\n  };\\n\\n  const logPractice \u003d (id: string, success: boolean) \u003d\u003e {\\n    setUserState(prev \u003d\u003e {\\n      const currentProgress \u003d prev.progress[id] || {\\n        itemId: id,\\n        nextReview: Date.now(),\\n        interval: 0,\\n        masteryLevel: 0,\\n        lastPracticed: Date.now()\\n      };\\n\\n      let newInterval \u003d currentProgress.interval;\\n      let newMastery \u003d currentProgress.masteryLevel;\\n\\n      if (success) {\\n        // Simple Spaced Repetition Logic\\n        if (newInterval \u003d\u003d\u003d 0) newInterval \u003d 1;\\n        else if (newInterval \u003d\u003d\u003d 1) newInterval \u003d 3;\\n        else newInterval \u003d Math.ceil(newInterval * 1.8);\\n        \\n        newMastery \u003d Math.min(newMastery + 1, 5);\\n      } else {\\n        newInterval \u003d 0; // Reset if forgotten\\n        newMastery \u003d Math.max(newMastery - 1, 0);\\n      }\\n\\n      // Calculate next review date\\n      const nextReviewDate \u003d new Date();\\n      nextReviewDate.setDate(nextReviewDate.getDate() + newInterval);\\n\\n      return {\\n        ...prev,\\n        progress: {\\n          ...prev.progress,\\n          [id]: {\\n            ...currentProgress,\\n            interval: newInterval,\\n            masteryLevel: newMastery,\\n            lastPracticed: Date.now(),\\n            nextReview: nextReviewDate.getTime()\\n          }\\n        }\\n      };\\n    });\\n  };\\n\\n  const getDueItems \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\\n    const now \u003d Date.now();\\n    return items.filter(item \u003d\u003e {\\n      if (!userState.savedItems.includes(item.id)) return false;\\n      const progress \u003d userState.progress[item.id];\\n      if (!progress) return true; // New items are due immediately\\n      return progress.nextReview \u003c\u003d now;\\n    });\\n  };\\n\\n  if (!isLoaded) return null;\\n\\n  return (\\n    \u003cStoreContext.Provider value\u003d{{\\n      items,\\n      savedItems: userState.savedItems,\\n      progress: userState.progress,\\n      toggleSaveItem,\\n      logPractice,\\n      getDueItems\\n    }}\u003e\\n      {children}\\n    \u003c/StoreContext.Provider\u003e\\n  );\\n};\\n\\nexport const useStore \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\\n  const context \u003d useContext(StoreContext);\\n  if (!context) throw new Error(\u0027useStore must be used within StoreProvider\u0027);\\n  return context;\\n};\\n\"}]},{\"path\":\"components/Layout.tsx\",\"generationType\":0,\"isDone\":true,\"description\":\"Main layout component wrapper\",\"diffs\":[{\"target\":\"\",\"replacement\":\"import React from \u0027react\u0027;\\nimport { Outlet, useLocation, useNavigate } from \u0027react-router-dom\u0027;\\nimport { Book, Home, Settings, Layers, ChevronLeft } from \u0027lucide-react\u0027;\\n\\nconst BottomNav \u003d () \u003d\u003e {\\n  const location \u003d useLocation();\\n  const navigate \u003d useNavigate();\\n\\n  const isActive \u003d (path: string) \u003d\u003e location.pathname \u003d\u003d\u003d path;\\n\\n  const NavItem \u003d ({ path, icon: Icon, label }: { path: string, icon: any, label: string }) \u003d\u003e (\\n    \u003cbutton\\n      onClick\u003d{() \u003d\u003e navigate(path)}\\n      className\u003d{`flex flex-col items-center justify-center w-full py-2 space-y-1 transition-colors ${\\n        isActive(path) ? \u0027text-primary-600\u0027 : \u0027text-slate-400 hover:text-slate-600\u0027\\n      }`}\\n    \u003e\\n      \u003cIcon size\u003d{24} strokeWidth\u003d{isActive(path) ? 2.5 : 2} /\u003e\\n      \u003cspan className\u003d\\\"text-xs font-medium\\\"\u003e{label}\u003c/span\u003e\\n    \u003c/button\u003e\\n  );\\n\\n  return (\\n    \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 bg-white border-t border-slate-200 safe-area-bottom pb-1 z-50\\\"\u003e\\n      \u003cdiv className\u003d\\\"flex justify-around max-w-md mx-auto\\\"\u003e\\n        \u003cNavItem path\u003d\\\"/\\\" icon\u003d{Home} label\u003d\\\"Focus\\\" /\u003e\\n        \u003cNavItem path\u003d\\\"/collection\\\" icon\u003d{Layer